000291r 2               ;; calculated by converting the ASCII value (57d) to its numerical value (9d) by subtracting
000291r 2               ;; 48d. Then multiplying by 2 (2*9 = 18) and then converting back to ASCII by adding 48d (which is
000291r 2               ;; only appropriate to convert a number to its ASCII character)
000291r 2               ;;
000291r 2               ;; ((57 - 48) * 2 + 48) but of course this doesn't work for numbers over 5..... you get an ASCII
